@startuml provider-access-gates
' The gate chain every LLM request passes, and the gate that does not exist in the gateway-only tier.
' Source of truth: docs/src/concepts/tenancy-and-tiers.md
!include _style.puml

skinparam ConditionEndStyle hline

|#F5F5F5|Both tiers|
start
:LLM request on the :8443 listener
qualified model **{providerRef}/{modelId}**;

if (caller identity?) then (mTLS client cert)
  :cert SAN yields
  (namespace, workload, kind)
  **full lifecycle tier**;
else (SA bearer token)
  :TokenReview yields
  namespace only
  **gateway-only tier**;
endif

if (Pod at source IP in that namespace?) then (no)
  :**401** unauthorized; <<#FFCDD2>>
  kill
else (yes)
endif

if (providerRef resolves to a ModelProvider?) then (no)
  :**400** invalid_request; <<#FFCDD2>>
  kill
else (yes)
endif

if (which tier?) then (gateway-only)
  :**Gate A does not exist here.**
  No Agent, AgentTask or AgentClass to consult; <<#F5F5F5>>
else (full lifecycle)
  |#E6E6FA|Full lifecycle tier only|
  if (**Gate A**\nproviderRef in workload spec.providers\n**and** in AgentClass.spec.allowedProviders?) then (no)
    :**403** access_denied; <<#FFCDD2>>
    kill
  else (yes)
  endif
  |#F5F5F5|Both tiers|
endif

if (**Gate B**\ncalling namespace in\nModelProvider.spec.allowedNamespaces?\nexact name or glob) then (no)
  :**403** access_denied; <<#FFCDD2>>
  kill
else (yes)
endif

if (**Gate C**\nmodelId in ModelProvider.spec.models?) then (no)
  :**400** invalid_request; <<#FFCDD2>>
  kill
else (yes)
endif

if (budget state for this namespace?) then (block)
  :**429** budget_exhausted
  Retry-After: next period reset
  **no fallback**; <<#FFCDD2>>
  kill
elseif (degrade) then
  :rewrite model to degradeTo;
else (warn / under cap)
endif

if (token bucket (namespace, model)?) then (empty)
  :**429** rate_limited
  Retry-After: short backoff; <<#FFCDD2>>
  kill
else (has tokens)
endif

:inject credential, strip prefix,
forward upstream
(fallback walk on upstream failure); <<#90EE90>>
stop

legend bottom
  **Gate A is the only tier conditional gate.** It is the one that needs an Agent
  and an AgentClass to read, so it has nothing to consult in the gateway-only tier.
  Gates B and C run identically for both tiers.
  **Gate C is not a tenancy boundary**: it resolves the model. An unknown modelId
  is a bad request (400), not a denied one (403).
endlegend
@enduml
